 *  GPS Module (NEO-6M / NEO-8M):
 *    VCC  → 3.3V or 5V
 *    GND  → GND
 *    TX   → Arduino RX1 (Pin 19 on Mega) / Pin 4 on Uno*
 *    RX   → Arduino TX1 (Pin 18 on Mega) / Pin 3 on Uno*
 *
 *  TF-Luna LiDAR:
 *    VCC  → 5V
 *    GND  → GND
 *    TX   → Arduino RX2 (Pin 17 on Mega) / Pin 6 on Uno*
 *    RX   → Arduino TX2 (Pin 16 on Mega) / Pin 5 on Uno*
 *
 *  SD Card Module (SPI):
 *    VCC  → 5V
 *    GND  → GND
 *    MOSI → Pin 51 (Mega) / Pin 11 (Uno)
 *    MISO → Pin 50 (Mega) / Pin 12 (Uno)
 *    SCK  → Pin 52 (Mega) / Pin 13 (Uno)
 *    CS   → Pin 53 (Mega) / Pin 10 (Uno)  ← SD_CS_PIN below
 *
 *  LED indicators (optional):
 *    GPS  lock LED  → Pin 7  (anode → pin, cathode → 220Ω → GND)
 *    SD   write LED → Pin 8
 *    ERR  LED       → Pin 9
 *
 *  * Uno/Nano: uses SoftwareSerial; only one SS port active at a time.
 *    For best results use Arduino Mega with hardware Serial1/Serial2.
 *
 *  LIBRARIES  (install via Library Manager):
 *    • TinyGPSPlus  by Mikal Hart
 *    • SD           by Arduino (built-in)
 *    • SPI          by Arduino (built-in)
 *    • SoftwareSerial (built-in, Uno only)
